<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I use a QMK keyboard with thumbclusters and as such I want to use Super and Hyper keys as extra modifiers for bindings in emacs.</p> <p>Super is default defined as the windows key and I have the APP key setup to be hyper via xmod: </p> <pre><code>keycode 135 = Hyper_L NoSymbol Hyper_L </code></pre> <p>I test this via using the global-set-key command interactively and when I press H-d emacs shows s-d</p> <p>I do dual boot and used Xah&#39;s tutorial for setting up the app key as hyper in windows (<a href="http://xahlee.info/emacs/emacs/emacs_hyper_super_keys.html">link</a>) and it works without issue. I&#39;m not concerned with making super work in windows as I am working towards 100% linux usage. </p> <p>Any ideas?</p> <p>&#x200B;</p> <pre><code> ## Output when pressing ALT ## KeyRelease event, serial 37, synthetic NO, window 0x2400001, root 0x1f2, subw 0x0, time 2951868, (604,430), root:(2094,517), state 0x8, keycode 108 (keysym 0xffea, Alt_R), same_screen YES, XLookupString gives 0 bytes: XFilterEvent returns: False ## OUTPUT WHEN PRESSING App/Hyper## KeyPress event, serial 37, synthetic NO, window 0x2400001, root 0x1f2, subw 0x0, time 2953012, (604,430), root:(2094,517), state 0x0, keycode 135 (keysym 0xffed, Hyper_L), same_screen YES, XLookupString gives 0 bytes: XmbLookupString gives 0 bytes: XFilterEvent returns: False ## OUTPUT WHEN PRESSING win/super KeyRelease event, serial 37, synthetic NO, window 0x2c00001, root 0x1f2, subw 0x0, time 5611274, (1139,149), root:(2629,236), state 0x40, keycode 133 (keysym 0xffec, Super_R), same_screen YES, XLookupString gives 0 bytes: XFilterEvent returns: False </code></pre> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/timmymayes"> /u/timmymayes </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/vwmwmq/emacs_reading_hyper_key_as_alt/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/vwmwmq/emacs_reading_hyper